snippet.description:
We just made ice cream on the jobsite with paint cans and a cement mixer, and all the flavors were construction inspired.
First up, ‚ÄúInsulation Sensation‚Äù -we added insulation pulled right out of the wall.
Half a can of Monster Pipeline Punch for caffeine, three packs of candy cigarettes, and four bags of Pop Rocks; so, your mouth will tingle like your skin does after installing insulation.
Next up, ‚ÄúAngry Roofer‚Äù-we poured in shingle grit, two scoops of roof tar, and then some crushed cinnamon candy- you‚Äôd be angry too if you had to spend all day on a hot roof.
And finally, for all your framers, ‚ÄúStud Muffin Swirl‚Äù. We dumped in blue chalk, a tube of construction adhesive, and some wood shavings.
We fired up the cement mixer, added in the cans, 300 pounds of ice, and rock salt.
It was so hot out you could actually see fog coming out of the mixer.
We couldn‚Äôt wait to open these up and see how they turned out.
All three flavors were amazing, but ‚ÄúStud Muffin Swirl‚Äù was my favorite.
Let us know in the comments. What construction flavors should we make next? @hausplans
